<A name=research></A>
<H2>Research Experience </H2>
<BR>
<H3>3/2011-6/2011 (Theoretical Computer Science) Primal-Dual Approximation Algorithm and Its Application </H3>
<H3>Independent, thesis project, supervised by Associate Prof. Zhenbo Wang, Mathematics Dept., Tsinghua University.</H3>
<UL>
  <LI>Designed unified framework and implementation of primal-dual approximation algorithms<br>
    which bounds NP-hard problems in P time.
  </UL>
<H3>7/2010-6/2011 (Pattern Recognition) Robust Classification under Least Median Criteria </H3>
<H3>Independent, thesis project, supervised by Associate Prof. Li Li, Inst. of Systems Eng., Tsinghua University.</H3>
<UL>
  <LI>Developed a new robust classification method (Median Loss-SVM) via modified Least Median Regression.
  <LI>Performed literature survey on Large Margin Classifiers.
  <LI>Derived a Lagrangian dual representation of Median Loss-SVM via Karush-Kuhn-Tucker conditions.
  <LI>Compared Median Loss-SVM with recent robust-SVM methods on nonlinear benchmark data sets.    
  </UL>
<H3>1/2010-6/2010 (Control Theory)  Stability Analysis of Continuous Switching Cone-wise Linear Systems</H3>
<H3>Independent, supervised by Prof. Shuning Wang, Inst. of Systems Eng., Tsinghua University. </H3>
<UL>
  <LI>Discovered a set of solvable smoothly connected differential equations with special features.  
  <LI>Designed an iterative local search algorithm, inspired by Markov Chain Monte Carlo I learnt in a graduate AI course.      
  <LI>The above solutions represented new conditions for analysis with minor extensions of recent  works.
</UL>
<H3><A name=publication></A></H3>
<HR style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0px; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
